CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 29, 1955, pg. A8 reads: "NAACP Protest Rally: 3,000 Hear Emmett Till Case Facts; Give;Urge United States to Act - District Attorney Regrets - District Attorney James F. Malone Jr. (right) greets Dr. Howard as Atty. Henry R. Smith Jr., state chairman of Pennsylvania's NAACP branches, watches. The DA stated that he regretted he wasn't in Mississippi to prosecute in Till case.  Lu Davenport, Malone's friend, told The Courier."
TitMainTitle: Dr. T. R. M. Howard shaking hands with Atty. James F. Malone Jr., with Judge Henry R. Smith standing in between them, standing in Soldier's and Sailor's Memorial Hall for NAACP protest rally
